  "intro": {
    "headline": "The Pulse of the South",
    "tagline": "Seasons of Salt and Sun",
    "paragraphs": [
      "Puglia doesn't do grey. The light here is sharp, golden, legendary — the kind photographers chase and painters try (and fail) to capture. This is the heel of Italy's boot, where the Adriatic meets the Ionian, where heat is a character in every story.",
      "The seasons here aren't theatrical — they're sensory. You smell them before you see them: wildflowers in spring, sea salt in summer, wood smoke in autumn. Winter is quieter, emptier, honest. The beaches belong to you. The masserie light fires.",
      "This is where you learn that sunshine isn't just weather — it's infrastructure."
    ],
    "hoverQuote": "In Puglia, you don't watch the sunset. You feel it on your skin.",
    "ctaText": "Slide through the seasons of the south →"
  },
